ss=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 856<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:02:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> <br>
1) He (and the dev team) view mages as a whining class with no specific examples or suggested solutions to problems.  As a result they don't even attempt to talk about changes to the mage class (other than nerfing things like CotH).<br>
<br>
2) Mages are viewed as middle of the stack in soloability post-50<br>
<br>
3) Dire charm &gt;&gt; mages in exp groups through to 60 (although they don't have the pet control experience yet, and they're presumably busy with croud control).<br>
<br>
<br>
Key issue, and one I keep bringing up, is #1.  We are a divisive community that can't even get agreement amongst ourselves to a list of problems, let alone suggested solutions.  We whine more than anything else.  And as this all goes on we're being relegated to an average damage dealer, a third level pet class, and middle of the pack soloer.  We're being indirectly nerfed out of existence.<br>
<br>
So we have 2 choices:<br>
<br>
1) Learn to work together and come to a real list of problems and a viable set of solutions that takes into consideration VI's perspective on us (not like most of the ones to date that are rediculous wish lists)<br>
<br>
2) Keep up what's going on and seal our fate<br>
<br>
Your choice.  All of our choices.  As of today, we are only unified in the whining about the VI posts.  I hope this changes soon.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qaedainmagikot>Qaedain Magikot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 432<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:04:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> I still say we should've sent the petition I wrote, and Rhion edited...By far it's had the most resounding support of any petition. It addresses pet damage, a few minor items, and pathing...<br>
<br>
3 simple paragraphs...No 10 page doctoral thesis...<br>
<br>
~shrug~ <p><img src=http://thraxtlar.50megs.com/Nerfbat.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uryuenom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryue NoM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:10:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> We are a divisive community that can't even get agreement amongst ourselves to a list of problems, let alone suggested solutions<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
I mostly browse the boards but I think this is probably the biggest reason why mages haven't gotten an upgrade in a while.<br>
<br>
Mages want pets to do more damage<br>
Mages want pets to have more HP's<br>
Mages want better nukes<br>
Mages want nukes other then fire/magic<br>
<br>
There's alot more, but the problem is, you really can't raise pet damage and raise nuking damage at the same time.  However, unless pet pathing and the &quot;idea out there&quot; that pets are bad for raids, having pets do more damage won't do much good for the high end mages.<br>
<br>
However, raising nuking damage then makes people wonder why they should play a wizard (though lure based spells help) if mages can do as much damage, have pets, have summoned items, etc.<br>
<br>
Plus, if they make non epic pets better then that means they have to upgrade the epic pet to be better then the non epic ones.  <br>
<br>
I think that is alot of why VI has a very hard time balancing mages the way they are.  They will really never make anyone happy.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuripedmoped.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euriped Moped</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:15:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yolora/zdance.gif height=40 width=40></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> Ryue: you're simply wrong.<br>
<br>
Magicians all agree that pathing <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> needs to be fixed</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. There are no if's, ands, or but. Pathing is horrible everywhere.<br>
<br>
