</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uryuenom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryue NoM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:28:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> Magicians all agree that pathing needs to be fixed. There are no if's, ands, or but. Pathing is horrible everywhere.<br>
<br>
I definately agree with that.  Ufortuantely that's not as an easy fix as everyone thinks.  Pets follow the same pathing as mobs and in order to fix it, every zone would have to be gone through and have the pathing changed.  Long process and I think its one that you'll never see happen as it really only effects 2 classes that rely on pets.<br>
<br>
Magicians all agree that every aspect of the magician class needs to scale up the same past 50, as it did before 50.<br>
<br>
Well, I would agree that pets need to be upgraded.  I agree that high level pets do need more HP's, need to hit harder, , need to be higher level, and need to be balanced better for high end raids.  However, I don't think you'll ever see DD damage changed or added too.  Once you start changing those, then you get into what happened when Kunark came out and Wizards through a fit because we did close to the same damage that their ice comet did.  <br>
<br>
MS3 would be a good spell to work with for a change of the mage class.  Allow it to summon a level 48ish mob that instead of having the skin of something there, actually is the mob itself.  That would be the exact same thing as the enchanters DC, but have less risk because of no chance of it being resisted.  If they don't want to make it MS3, make it a AA skill that summons a high level &quot;Demonlord&quot; pet or something like that.<br>
<br>
However, if you do that, you really trivialize the epic and that would have to be changed.  Its MUCH eaiser to sit and get exp in order to get that skill rather then sit and work on getting everything you need for the epic.<br>
<br>
Every other class in the game scales properly, EVERY SINGLE ONE. Magicians are the only class that does not receive significant upgrades past 50. <br>
<br>
Druids are hurting post 50 and even more after SoL as far as raiding goes.  I've played both a mage and a druid to 54+ and I know the druids pain.  <br>
<br>
Just roll that around your mind. <br>
<br>
Oh, I have.  I stopped playing my Mage when DAoC came out (wish I hadn't, but I was burnt out).  I'm having a hard time deciding to come back or not as I love EQ, but I don't want to get sucked in again.  The mage was fun, but I hated trying to look for a group all the time with little or no luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 1147<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:28:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1) He (and the dev team) view mages as a whining class with no specific examples or suggested solutions to problems. As a result they don't even attempt to talk about changes to the mage class (other than nerfing things like CotH).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I seriously doubt this.  They see the most vocal of their playerbase as rather whiny in general, I'm sure mages are nothing special.  Absor made much similar comments to wizards when the Team made that large adjustment to the high end melee tables. <p><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE><center><b>Goladus Mistrydia</b></font><br>
