<a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8506">Profile</a> | Solusek Ro</font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 1148<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:38:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Key issue, and one I keep bringing up, is #1. We are a divisive community that can't even get agreement amongst ourselves to a list of problems, let alone suggested solutions. We whine more than anything else. And as this all goes on we're being relegated to an average damage dealer, a third level pet class, and middle of the pack soloer. We're being indirectly nerfed out of existence.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->The other thing you're missing is that reaching an agreement takes time and effort, it doesn't just happen, and stuff like this just adds fuel to the fire.  Continuing to bring up issue number 1 doesn't solve anything.  The only way to solve issue number 1 is to actively and positively work toward a solution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 9:55:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> I would also like to see better pet pathing but for me, it's on the bottom of my list.  Why?  Because I personally think its too big of a project and one that Verant will never take on.  <br>
<br>
Read the comments made about moving the Wizzy spires in East Karana.  That task seems simple enough ... but it means (according to Absor) having to download a 6 megabyte patch, and something that Verant simply will not do.<br>
<br>
Yes in some zones pet pathing means pets are allowed or pets are not allowed ... but the amount of zones where pets are an absolute no no are the minority to zones where they're fine to have up.<br>
<br>
So I would rather see Mages as a whole concentating our efforts on showing Verant how badly we are in need of an upgrade of some sort to stay viable as a class in this game.  Our utility is fine at the moment.  I can even live with disabled CoH in some Luclin zones.  What we need are pets that can put a dent in MOBs with incredibly high AC.  From what I can tell, pets add to about half the DPS of a Mage's damage.  Without the pet sustaining that, Mages fall drastically on the usefulness scale.  After all, we are THE pet class ... with a degree of useful utility.<br>
<br>
AbFab - I personally am a little upset that Absor chose to respond to that person's submission ... because I'm sure he's recieved hundereds of others from Mages that used more tact in their posts and were more clear and concise about our problems.  The only conclusion I can make it the post pissed him off ... and I'm not so sure that's a bad thing.<br>
<br>
I say this because finally some discussion about the Mage class is coming up again on the EQ forums.  And it opens the door for us to try to get something done.  So to answer your question ... I think it has helped.  As long as we don't drop the ball ... and that we try to turn his initial negativity into something constructive that he can take to the development team.<br>
<br>
 <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24305>Kalamos</a></b><br>58th High Elf Conjurer<br>The Seventh Hammer</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A> at: 1/30/02 10:20:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarzan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/02 10:05:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has Alan's comments helped?</span><hr size=1> Absor and the rest are probabaly numb by now from the various classes clamoring about how they are weak and nerfed, especially in the post 50 game.  And if you are not in their holy trio, you have a right to angry.  Knowing that this is going to be a melee based game and the trinity is the base of it all, we are left with the choice to either suck it up and be the one or two nontrinity classes on a raid (that is if there are open slots), start a trinity class or go to a different gaming system.<br>
<br>
